<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="166" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,513,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[851,919,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">pedis-</emphasis>
(= foot), with a Latin suffix, 
<emphasis box="[1245,1294,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">-alis</emphasis>
, referring to the foot-shaped cucullus of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
